help.name: daily

help.name: slots
help.description: A slots machine to spin on and bet your treats!

help.name: transfer
help.description: The `transfer` command allows you to give some of your treats to another user.

help.name: treats
help.description: The `treats` command displays a users treats, yabe's premium currency!
help.usage: treats <optional mention to get another users treats balance>

help.name: work
help.description: The `work` command allows you to work for some treats!

help.name: 8ball
help.description: Gives a totally ~~random~~ calculated answer to your question

help.name: roll
help.description: The `roll` command rolls a specified number of die with a specified number of sides.

help.name: owofy
help.description: The `owofy` command takes text and owofies it! Just try it out and you'll get the gist of it.
help.usage: owofy <text to put through the owofication process>

help.name: channel
help.description: The `channel` command gives information about the current channel.

help.name: roles
help.description: The `roles` command displays all roles below the `Mom` role.

help.name: uptime
help.description: Allows you to view how long mom has been running.

help.name: whois
help.description: The `whois` command displays a list of all people with a requested role.

help.name: eval
help.description: Evaluates javascript code

help.name: ban
help.description: The `ban` command requires `Ban Members` permission. It allows you to ban a specified user.

help.name: kick
help.description: The `kick` command requires `Kick Members` permission. It allows you to kick a specified user.

help.name: reload
help.description: reloads commands

help.name: rem
help.description: The `rem` command require the `Manage Messages` permission. It removes a given amount of message, to clean up chats.
help.usage: rem <amount of messages to be removed>

help.name: snipe
help.description: [CENSORED]

help.name: bassboost
help.description: The `bassboost` command allows you to bassboost the current song

help.name: earrape
help.description: The `earrape` command does just that, earrapes you on the current song

help.name: leave
help.description: The `leave` command makes mom leave the current guilds vc

help.name: loop
help.description: The `loop` command allows you to loop the current queue

help.name: lyrics
help.description: The `lyrics` command allows you to view lyrics for the currently playing song if any lyrics are available

help.name: normal
help.description: The `normal` command reverts all sound settings to the default for the current playing track.

help.name: nowplaying
help.description: The `nowplaying` command allows you to see the currently playing song

help.name: play
help.description: The `play` command allows you to play a song to add to the queue

help.name: queue
help.description: The `queue` command allows you to view the current queue of music

help.name: remove
help.description: The `remove` command allows you to remove certain songs in the queue

help.name: removedupes
help.description: The `removedupes` command allows you to remove all duplicate songs from the queue

help.name: removerange
help.description: The `removerange` command allows you to remove a range of songs from the queue
help.usage: removerange <starting range> <endingrange(optional)/defaults to end of queue>

help.name: search
help.description: The `search` command allows you to search songs and then choose which you want to play/add to queue

help.name: shuffle
help.description: The `shuffle` command allows you to shuffle the current queue

help.name: skip
help.description: The `skip` command allows you to skip songs, once three or more people are in the voice channel, will be decided by vote.

help.name: volume
help.description:
The `volume` command allows you to change the volume of mom's music. `NOTE: Requires mom premium`
Please be aware that changing the stream volume will lower the quality of the music due to encoding rules

help.name: prefix
help.description: The `prefix` command changes your guild's prefix to pretty much anything.

help.name: welcome
help.description:
The `welcome` command allows you to set a custom message. Use `{{}}` in your message to mention the user on join, and to put channels in your message, put the id of the channel in double brackets, `[[channel id here]]`
Example: 'Welcome {{}}, please read [[6549519484921321]]. We love you :)'
help.usage: welcome <enable/disable> <mention welcome channel> <message to welcome new users>

help.name: addrole
help.description: Allows mom to give you the provided role

help.name: help
help.description: The `help` command displays a help menu, which contains a list of commands and a way to find further help.

help.name: invite
help.description: The `invite` command sends an instant invite for mom straight to your own server(s).

help.name: ping
help.description: The `ping` command returns the client's ping to the Discord API and the users ping to the client's host server.

help.name: remind
help.description:
The `remind` command allows you to set, remove, and view reminders!

PLEASE NOTE, YOU MUST ALLOW DM'S FROM THE GUILD YOU SET THE REMINDER IN TO GET THE REMINDER!

Command parses time as such, a number before a letter denotes an amount of time, for examples, `5d` is parsed as 5 days. So a valid input would be `mom remind 5d:5h:30m fix my pc` which translates to 'In five days, 5 hours, and 30 minutes, remind me to fix my pc!'

Run `mom remind example` for all rules!
